article.headline: New Orleans 51, New Mexico State 37
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Victor Brown scored 14 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead New Orleans to a 51-37 win over New Mexico State Thursday night. Bill McDade added 11 points for the Privateers (12-11, 6-4 Sun Belt Conference) and Bo McCalebb dished out five assists. New Mexico State (10-11, 4-6) got 10 points from James Moore before he fouled out with 6:57 left in the game. He got all five fouls in the second half. Moore was the only Aggie to score in double digits. Kelsey Crooks pulled down six rebounds for the Aggies. Moore brought the Aggies to within 3 points -- 23-20 -- in the second half, but the Privateers retaliated with a 5-0 run. New Mexico State has lost three of its last four games against New Orleans. New Orleans held New Mexico State to a season-low 37 points, holding the Aggies scoreless over the first 6:20 of the game. It was also the lowest scoring game for the Aggies since the 1964-65 season, when NMSU lost to New Mexico 62-37. The Privateers' defense limited the Aggies to 28 percent shooting from the field and they finished 13-of-46. New Orleans also dominated the rebounding battle, grabbing 47 while New Mexico State had 32. Both teams struggled from outside the arc. The Aggies hit just 1 of 13 3-pointers. The Privateers hit just 3 of 14 3-pointers.
